## AWS

This capstone will challenge you to do the following:

* Launch and configure an AWS Cloud9 integrated development environment (IDE) instance.  
* Transform CSV-formatted data files to the Apache Parquet format and upload them to Amazon S3.  
* Create an AWS Glue crawler to infer the structure of the data.  
* Use Amazon Athena to query the data.  
* Create an Athena view.  
* Run queries on Athena view to analyse data.

![][image1]

## Data source

[https://www.seaaroundus.org/data/\#/eez](https://www.seaaroundus.org/data/#/eez)

* The first file contains data from all open seas areas.  
* The second file contains data from a single open seas area in the Pacific ocean, referred to as Pacific, Western Central, which is not far from Fiji and many other countries.  
* The third file contains data from the EEZ of a single country (Fiji), which is near the Pacific, Western Central open seas area.

# Goal of the project

The goal of this project is to practice data extraction and manipulation in AWS services. Three separate csv files are converted, transformed, and loaded into S3 buckets. Queries are made on these files to analyze the data.

## Custom queries

1. **Get the average tonnes and landed value per fishing sector:**

select fishing\_sector,  
	avg(tonnes) as tonnes\_avg,  
	cast(cast(avg(landed\_value) as double) as decimal(38,2)) as dollars\_avg  
from fishdb.data\_source\_wb44u5  
where year \> 2010  
group by fishing\_sector  
![][image16]  
Industrial sector had both the highest average tonnes and dollars per fishing after 2010\. Artisanal fishing is both smaller in volume and in value due to that they use low-technology, traditional fishing practices.

**2\. Get heaviest discard catches per country in 2011**  
select fishing\_entity as Country,  
catch\_type,  
	max(tonnes) as max\_tonnes  
from data\_source\_wb44u5  
where catch\_type \= 'Discards' and year \= 2011  
group by fishing\_entity, catch\_type  
order by max(tonnes) desc 

![][image17]  
Russia, Peru, Vietnam had the highest discards fishings in 2011\.

**3\. Get most fished fish types in 1950**  
select sum(tonnes) as total\_tonnes,  
	common\_name  
from data\_source\_wb44u5  
where year \= 1950 and common\_name is not null  
group by common\_name  
order by sum(tonnes) desc  
![][image18]  
Skipjack tuna, emperors, and not identified fishes were the most fished types in 1950\.
